        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>When troubleshooting an AC system leak at the thermistor, it is not always necessary to replace
                    the thermistor. If after following the Service Procedure below it is determined that the thermistor
                    needs to be replaced, a new thermistor design (Figure 1) is available and interchangeable with the
                    old design thermistor (Figure 2).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0616051" figsize="pg-wide">
